# Design Tokens

This project uses a design token system defined in `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`.

## Token Reference

When implementing UI, use these token names rather than hardcoded values:

### Colors
- `color-primary` - Primary brand color
- `color-secondary` - Secondary brand color
- `color-background` - Page background
- `color-surface` - Card/panel backgrounds
- `color-text` - Primary text
- `color-text-secondary` - Muted text
- `color-error` - Error states
- `color-success` - Success states
- `color-warning` - Warning states

### Typography
- `text-xs` through `text-5xl` - Font sizes
- `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold` - Weights

### Spacing
- `spacing-1` through `spacing-16` - Spacing scale

### Border Radius
- `radius-sm`, `radius-md`, `radius-lg`, `radius-xl`, `radius-full`

### Shadows
- `shadow-sm`, `shadow-md`, `shadow-lg`, `shadow-xl`

## Implementation Guidelines

### Tailwind CSS
```jsx
// Use semantic class names that map to tokens
<button className="bg-primary text-white rounded-md px-4 py-2">
```

### CSS Variables
```css
.button {
  background: var(--color-primary);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  padding: var(--spacing-2) var(--spacing-4);
}
```

## When Building UI

1. Reference tokens from `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`
2. Use token names in ASCII mockups (in feature specs)
3. Implement using actual token values
4. Document token usage in component docs

## Updates

When tokens change:
1. Update `.specs/design-system/tokens.md`
2. Update this rule if token names change
3. Run `/design-tokens` to sync changes
